17/02/2006
WASHINGTON, United States -- Croatia hopes to become a NATO member by 2008, Minister of Foreign Affairs and EU Integration Kolinda Grabar-Kitarovic said on Thursday (16 February) after a meeting with US Undersecretary of State Nicholas Burns.
Grabar-Kitarovic's official visit is aimed at strengthening ties with the US administration in the area of military co-operation.
In other news Thursday, Croatian President Stipe Mesic said he is concerned about Italy's hints that it might delay or even suspend Croatia's EU accession bid if bilateral disputes are not resolved.
He called for an atmosphere of understanding in which compromise can be reached.
(Vjesnik, Novi List - 17/02/06;
HINA, HRT - 16/02/06)
